1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 10=

3
00:01:43,820 --> 00:01:52,020
(Day Three After the Comeback)

4
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:53,420
Ms. Lin,

5
00:01:56,860 --> 00:01:57,780
after last night,

6
00:01:57,780 --> 00:01:59,140
our numbers have finally picked up.

7
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,540
Dingqi Platform pushed it.

8
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:02,260
Drunk Old Friend has gripping twists,

9
00:02:02,260 --> 00:02:03,290
and people just can't stop reading.

10
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:05,220
New subscriptions have
already passed thirty thousand.

11
00:02:05,220 --> 00:02:05,540
Ms. Lin.

12
00:02:05,620 --> 00:02:07,760
Also, the comments
under Drunk Old Friend have exploded.

13
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:09,940
And WeChat has pushed our novel, too.

14
00:02:10,044 --> 00:02:10,980
What does this mean?

15
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:12,980
This is what you call
small steps building

16
00:02:13,180 --> 00:02:14,260
into a long journey.

17
00:02:15,220 --> 00:02:16,100
How are things now?

18
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:18,100
We're still in first place.

19
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:19,533
Shattered Six States is second.

20
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:21,340
(Drunk Old Friend real-time popularity)

21
00:02:21,340 --> 00:02:22,460
(Shattered Six States
real-time popularity)

22
00:02:22,580 --> 00:02:24,020
We're pulling ahead.

23
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:26,530
We can release the next story preview

24
00:02:26,530 --> 00:02:27,340
that Gu Yan prepared.

25
00:02:27,488 --> 00:02:28,540
Let's push another wave.

26
00:02:28,622 --> 00:02:30,088
- Got it, Ms. Lin.
- Got it, Ms. Lin.

27
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:30,580
Naobaijin,

28
00:02:30,888 --> 00:02:31,700
hurry it up.

29
00:02:31,980 --> 00:02:36,260
(Chapter 183, Story Preview. Please
bookmark and vote for Drunk Old Friend.)

30
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:41,860
Lin Zhanqiao really
knows how to play this.

31
00:02:42,311 --> 00:02:43,288
You all saw that, right?

32
00:02:43,340 --> 00:02:44,020
Yeah, we saw it.

33
00:02:45,740 --> 00:02:46,740
Lin Zhanqiao doesn't

34
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:49,140
have much money, but she
is still pouring it into marketing.

35
00:02:49,140 --> 00:02:51,100
She's all in with Gu Yan,

36
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:52,820
win or lose.

37
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:55,300
That's not her usual style.

38
00:02:55,540 --> 00:02:57,444
If you said Zhao Lanxin,
I'd believe it more.

39
00:02:58,460 --> 00:02:59,060
Jealous?

40
00:02:59,266 --> 00:03:01,288
She never went this hard for you,
did she?

41
00:03:01,660 --> 00:03:02,580
Don't be ridiculous.

42
00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:04,980
I never gave her that kind of chance.

43
00:03:04,980 --> 00:03:05,580
As a man,

44
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:07,980
why would you want someone else
to spend money fighting for you?

45
00:03:08,060 --> 00:03:09,180
Go find Lin Zhanqiao?

46
00:03:09,460 --> 00:03:10,577
Depends on my mood.

47
00:03:29,740 --> 00:03:30,900
So what do we need to see

48
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:32,620
before we can call it settled?

49
00:03:33,940 --> 00:03:35,580
I'd say it's already clear.

50
00:03:36,380 --> 00:03:37,460
So,

51
00:03:38,020 --> 00:03:39,420
we won?

52
00:03:41,022 --> 00:03:42,266
A comeback from behind.

53
00:03:43,420 --> 00:03:44,300
Drunk Old Friend

54
00:03:44,466 --> 00:03:45,533
has taken the top spot.

55
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:53,380
Congratulations.

56
00:03:54,420 --> 00:03:54,900
Thanks.

57
00:04:00,620 --> 00:04:04,500
- Gu Yan!
- Gu Yan!

58
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:16,340
(Drunk Old Friend takes the top spot!)

59
00:04:22,222 --> 00:04:23,866
So, how is it? Is Wang Hai first?

60
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:24,540
First.

61
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:25,420
The He is second.

62
00:04:26,980 --> 00:04:28,340
Is he staying in first?

63
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:29,700
No idea.

64
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:31,540
The internet says Gu Yan is number one.

65
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:35,180
This guy's got it.

66
00:04:36,980 --> 00:04:37,940
Hey, what's wrong?

67
00:04:38,220 --> 00:04:39,177
You're not happy?

68
00:04:40,060 --> 00:04:40,740
I am.

69
00:04:41,340 --> 00:04:42,260
I'm happy for Gu Yan.

70
00:04:43,340 --> 00:04:44,900
Boss, terminal 16 crashed.

71
00:04:59,740 --> 00:05:00,500
You're not happy?

72
00:05:01,933 --> 00:05:03,244
It just doesn't feel fair.

73
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:07,340
Things aren't always fair,

74
00:05:07,822 --> 00:05:09,600
and they don't always go your way.

75
00:05:11,260 --> 00:05:11,780
Cheer up.

76
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:14,260
Alright.

77
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:16,900
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

78
00:05:37,980 --> 00:05:39,620
This rear-view mirror is pretty flashy.

79
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:41,600
The car is really yours?

80
00:05:42,620 --> 00:05:43,340
Of course.

81
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:44,733
Want to see the registration?

82
00:05:44,780 --> 00:05:46,666
I've already signed up for ride-sharing.

83
00:05:46,688 --> 00:05:48,333
It should be approved tonight.

84
00:05:50,020 --> 00:05:51,180
Driving a car like this

85
00:05:51,260 --> 00:05:52,420
and doing rideshare,

86
00:05:52,822 --> 00:05:54,044
what are you after?

87
00:05:54,244 --> 00:05:55,540
Trying out a different lifestyle,

88
00:05:55,660 --> 00:05:56,700
or picking up girls?

89
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:58,022
What do you think?

90
00:05:59,044 --> 00:06:00,822
How many people have
you added on WeChat?

91
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:02,180
You're my first passenger.

92
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:03,380
Others didn't dare get in.

93
00:06:04,820 --> 00:06:05,980
Do I look like a bad guy?

94
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:06,860
You

95
00:06:07,111 --> 00:06:08,711
must be in your forties, right?

96
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:10,540
Think I'm old?

97
00:06:17,020 --> 00:06:21,340
(Cai Zhangzhu: Are you free tonight?
I have a few questions to ask.)

98
00:06:26,580 --> 00:06:27,533
Add me on WeChat.

99
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:29,177
I'll give you a discount next time.

100
00:06:29,260 --> 00:06:29,620
Thanks.

101
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:36,620
Bye.

102
00:06:36,740 --> 00:06:37,020
Bye.

103
00:06:43,940 --> 00:06:47,780
(Cai Zhangzhu: Are you free tonight?
I have a few questions to ask.)

104
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:56,620
(Legend: I'll message you
when I'm done tonight.)

105
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:01,660
Ms. Lin,

106
00:07:02,260 --> 00:07:02,940
are you leaving?

107
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,340
One thing is finally off my mind.

108
00:07:05,660 --> 00:07:07,111
I'm going back to get some rest.

109
00:07:07,420 --> 00:07:08,020
How about

110
00:07:08,444 --> 00:07:10,044
having dinner before you go?

111
00:07:11,060 --> 00:07:11,900
Not tonight.

112
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,010
We'll have plenty of
chances to eat together.

113
00:07:14,020 --> 00:07:14,810
No need to rush today.

114
00:07:14,810 --> 00:07:16,620
But shouldn't we celebrate today?

115
00:07:17,420 --> 00:07:18,820
This is just the first step.

116
00:07:19,420 --> 00:07:20,180
When we finish it,

117
00:07:20,260 --> 00:07:21,444
we'll celebrate properly.

118
00:07:21,688 --> 00:07:23,133
You should head back and rest, too.

119
00:07:23,140 --> 00:07:24,488
We will keep going tomorrow.

120
00:07:24,540 --> 00:07:24,940
Bye.

121
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:26,700
Bye.

122
00:07:28,060 --> 00:07:28,740
Bye, Ms. Lin.

123
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:29,420
Ms. Lin.

124
00:07:31,180 --> 00:07:31,780
Bye, Ms. Lin.

125
00:09:16,620 --> 00:09:17,740
I got off work early today.

126
00:09:17,860 --> 00:09:19,620
He asked if I wanted to meet for dinner.

127
00:09:23,860 --> 00:09:25,060
Of course not.

128
00:09:25,155 --> 00:09:26,755
You can't just go whenever he calls.

129
00:09:26,866 --> 00:09:28,688
Set a time and have him come to you.

130
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,177
Are you coming back for dinner tonight?

131
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:36,260
No.

132
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:37,380
I have plans.

133
00:09:44,940 --> 00:09:50,060
(Lin Zhanqiao: Not today. Another time.)

134
00:09:59,822 --> 00:10:00,688
I'm back.

135
00:10:03,580 --> 00:10:04,980
Finally. Come on, hurry.

136
00:10:05,180 --> 00:10:05,460
Quick.

137
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:07,260
Sit down and eat.

138
00:10:08,288 --> 00:10:09,355
To celebrate your victory,

139
00:10:09,377 --> 00:10:10,866
San Mei has been cooking all afternoon.

140
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,180
Didn't expect you to come back so early.

141
00:10:13,180 --> 00:10:14,020
Thought you'd be out with Ms. Lin,

142
00:10:14,020 --> 00:10:15,422
having a celebration dinner first.

143
00:10:15,780 --> 00:10:17,460
No, there wasn't any dinner tonight.

144
00:10:17,860 --> 00:10:19,780
We just celebrated a bit this afternoon.

145
00:10:19,780 --> 00:10:21,020
What? No celebration dinner?

146
00:10:21,140 --> 00:10:22,133
Is everyone that busy?

147
00:10:22,380 --> 00:10:23,220
I guess so.

148
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:25,210
It's my first time,

149
00:10:25,210 --> 00:10:27,420
but for Ms. Lin,
she's probably had plenty.

150
00:10:28,580 --> 00:10:30,020
I was all ready today,

151
00:10:30,020 --> 00:10:31,300
thinking Ms. Lin would come too.

152
00:10:31,620 --> 00:10:32,780
See? She planned it well.

153
00:10:32,860 --> 00:10:34,260
Too bad Ms. Lin didn't come.

154
00:10:35,140 --> 00:10:36,700
Forget it. We'll celebrate ourselves.

155
00:10:36,777 --> 00:10:37,800
- Come on.
- Let's go.

156
00:10:43,660 --> 00:10:45,130
I just threw this together.

157
00:10:45,130 --> 00:10:46,733
Nothing compared to those big banquets.

158
00:10:47,260 --> 00:10:48,380
What do big banquets matter?

159
00:10:48,860 --> 00:10:49,540
Once I make money,

160
00:10:49,622 --> 00:10:51,600
I'll take you all to the best,
most expensive places.

161
00:10:51,620 --> 00:10:52,780
Like anyone cares.

162
00:10:53,140 --> 00:10:54,140
Honestly, food outside

163
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:55,500
isn't as good as San Mei's cooking.

164
00:10:55,711 --> 00:10:57,260
Besides, you're getting too famous.

165
00:10:57,260 --> 00:10:59,088
That might not be
a good thing for the internet cafe.

166
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:00,260
But you won.

167
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:01,700
We're just happy for you.

168
00:11:02,260 --> 00:11:02,660
Right?

169
00:11:02,860 --> 00:11:03,180
Yeah.

170
00:11:04,380 --> 00:11:05,220
Come on, cheers.

171
00:11:06,660 --> 00:11:07,140
Thank you.

172
00:11:07,620 --> 00:11:09,300
No need to thank us.

173
00:11:58,780 --> 00:12:00,060
Another drink.

174
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:03,060
Here, take it.

175
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:06,140
Congratulations, Editor Lin.

176
00:12:06,140 --> 00:12:07,180
Why didn't you call

177
00:12:07,180 --> 00:12:08,100
and show off a bit?

178
00:12:10,140 --> 00:12:10,820
Where are you?

179
00:12:11,140 --> 00:12:11,740
Got time?

180
00:12:12,088 --> 00:12:13,100
Come chat for a bit.

181
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:14,060
Sure, come over.

182
00:12:14,060 --> 00:12:14,980
It's lively here.

183
00:12:15,140 --> 00:12:16,644
There are drinks and pretty company.

184
00:12:17,940 --> 00:12:20,620
Cheers.

185
00:12:21,980 --> 00:12:23,422
You guys go ahead. I'll make a call.

186
00:12:23,740 --> 00:12:24,210
Alright.

187
00:12:24,210 --> 00:12:25,220
Come by later, Mr. He.

188
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:26,300
See you later, Mr. He.

189
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:27,466
What I wanted to tell you is,

190
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:29,533
regarding what happened today,

191
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:32,140
Mr. Fan played a huge part.

192
00:12:32,940 --> 00:12:33,980
I don't know why

193
00:12:33,980 --> 00:12:35,580
he helped Gu Yan and me so much.

194
00:12:36,866 --> 00:12:38,860
But if it's because of your
relationship with Dai Shan

195
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:40,244
that he misunderstood something,

196
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:42,100
or if he has something against you,

197
00:12:43,060 --> 00:12:44,100
shouldn't you find a chance

198
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:45,200
to clear things up with him?

199
00:12:45,244 --> 00:12:47,111
Tell him you two are
just putting on an act.

200
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:48,140
Otherwise,

201
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,220
I'm worried

202
00:12:49,220 --> 00:12:50,933
that if he keeps
targeting you like this,

203
00:12:50,977 --> 00:12:52,180
it'll be thankless for you

204
00:12:52,266 --> 00:12:53,533
to keep writing later.

205
00:12:58,020 --> 00:12:59,540
I'm only reminding you out of goodwill.

206
00:13:00,020 --> 00:13:00,740
Nothing else.

207
00:13:03,780 --> 00:13:04,700
Come on, Lin Zhanqiao.

208
00:13:04,822 --> 00:13:05,933
You don't seriously think

209
00:13:05,940 --> 00:13:07,577
I care about being
first or second, do you?

210
00:13:08,260 --> 00:13:09,288
If anything, it's you.

211
00:13:09,780 --> 00:13:12,300
You keep pushing me over and over
to break up with Dai Shan.

212
00:13:12,820 --> 00:13:15,180
So is Mr. Fan jealous, or are you?

213
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:19,100
Is something wrong with you?

214
00:13:19,580 --> 00:13:20,860
Do you have to

215
00:13:20,940 --> 00:13:22,688
get all narcissistic
every chance you get?

216
00:13:23,180 --> 00:13:24,460
So the people out there

217
00:13:24,820 --> 00:13:25,820
have to put up with you

218
00:13:25,820 --> 00:13:27,300
just because you're He Han?

219
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:28,644
Well, if it's not, just say so.

220
00:13:28,650 --> 00:13:31,222
Why are you reacting so strongly?
What else am I supposed to think?

221
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:49,580
Come on, let's liven things up.

222
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:52,260
Tonight, we have to enjoy ourselves.

223
00:13:52,340 --> 00:13:53,540
It's on me!

224
00:13:53,740 --> 00:13:55,020
Thank you, Mr. He.

225
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:56,340
Thank you.

226
00:13:56,622 --> 00:13:58,777
- Thank you, Mr. He Han.
- Come on, drink up.

227
00:14:18,555 --> 00:14:19,622
You just got back,

228
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:21,111
or you're going out again?

229
00:14:21,380 --> 00:14:22,430
You haven't even changed.

230
00:14:22,620 --> 00:14:23,460
I'm going out.

231
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:25,711
Be careful at night, then.

232
00:14:26,540 --> 00:14:28,140
He didn't say what time.

233
00:14:28,140 --> 00:14:29,860
He just said he'd find me
when he's done.

234
00:14:30,460 --> 00:14:30,860
A friend?

235
00:14:31,660 --> 00:14:32,220
Boyfriend?

236
00:14:34,460 --> 00:14:34,940
Friend.

237
00:14:39,660 --> 00:14:40,500
I'm back.

238
00:14:42,340 --> 00:14:42,940
Careful.

239
00:14:45,580 --> 00:14:46,060
Who are you?

240
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:47,620
I'm Zhangzhu.

241
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:49,860
So you're Zhangzhu?

242
00:14:50,620 --> 00:14:51,180
It's okay.

243
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:55,740
I'm Zhou Mei.

244
00:14:56,540 --> 00:14:57,420
Hi, Zhou Mei.

245
00:14:58,820 --> 00:15:00,020
You're so pretty.

246
00:15:00,555 --> 00:15:01,777
Get me a glass of water.

247
00:15:02,220 --> 00:15:02,540
Okay.

248
00:15:05,380 --> 00:15:06,500
Who did you have dinner with?

249
00:15:07,180 --> 00:15:08,060
I ate alone.

250
00:15:16,220 --> 00:15:17,500
You drank this much alone?

251
00:15:20,711 --> 00:15:22,466
Because I was waiting for someone.

252
00:15:23,422 --> 00:15:24,888
That's why I drank so much.

253
00:15:36,260 --> 00:15:37,700
Hello, ma'am. Here's your menu.

254
00:15:38,820 --> 00:15:39,220
Thank you.

255
00:15:41,980 --> 00:15:43,380
Is this the menu Lawyer Bei ordered?

256
00:15:43,660 --> 00:15:45,220
Yes. It was ordered a month ago.

257
00:15:46,022 --> 00:15:47,511
Bring me a glass of wine first.

258
00:15:47,733 --> 00:15:48,733
Okay.

259
00:15:51,260 --> 00:15:52,180
A month ago,

260
00:15:52,340 --> 00:15:53,940
we agreed to have dinner together today.

261
00:15:55,460 --> 00:15:57,180
So you waited for him all night,

262
00:15:57,288 --> 00:15:58,533
and he didn't come?

263
00:16:01,177 --> 00:16:02,577
Did he do it on purpose?

264
00:16:03,860 --> 00:16:05,300
I know he wouldn't forget.

265
00:16:08,222 --> 00:16:10,140
He's not the kind of person
who forgets dates.

266
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:16,100
He chose not to come.

267
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:18,380
To punish me.

268
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:22,220
To tell me I was too reckless

269
00:16:23,266 --> 00:16:25,644
and shouldn't have
gone downstairs to his place.

270
00:16:39,340 --> 00:16:42,660
♪First Time in love♪

271
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:45,540
Hello, ma'am.

272
00:16:45,577 --> 00:16:47,180
May I ask if Mr. Bei is still coming?

273
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:49,133
Would you like us to
serve the dishes first?

274
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:50,780
No.

275
00:16:51,422 --> 00:16:53,466
He had something
come up and couldn't make it.

276
00:16:54,177 --> 00:16:55,088
Just bring the bill.

277
00:16:55,620 --> 00:16:56,900
Mr. Bei has already paid.

278
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:58,580
♪Yet no one will ever know♪

279
00:16:58,580 --> 00:16:59,340
He's already paid?

280
00:16:59,740 --> 00:17:00,300
When?

281
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:01,700
His assistant,

282
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:03,580
Mr. Zhang, called to settle it for him.

283
00:17:07,940 --> 00:17:08,260
Alright.

284
00:17:08,780 --> 00:17:09,180
Thank you.

285
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:15,860
♪And here you are♪

286
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:21,140
♪Calling my name in the air♪

287
00:17:23,100 --> 00:17:25,060
If you still deal
with someone like that,

288
00:17:26,660 --> 00:17:28,260
you're doing yourself a disservice.

289
00:17:28,780 --> 00:17:31,500
♪I see you at the end♪

290
00:17:31,500 --> 00:17:32,540
But who isn't like that?

291
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:36,740
The one who leaves
you shattered every time

292
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:39,380
is the one you still can't help loving

293
00:17:40,533 --> 00:17:42,577
once you pull yourself back together.

294
00:17:56,288 --> 00:17:57,911
Do you have a boyfriend?

295
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:00,540
No.

296
00:18:05,377 --> 00:18:07,400
You don't happen
to like He Han too, right?

297
00:18:10,260 --> 00:18:11,100
Let me tell you,

298
00:18:11,422 --> 00:18:12,900
He Han belongs to Lin Zhanqiao.

299
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:14,460
We've broken up for good.

300
00:18:16,900 --> 00:18:18,260
I've been meaning to ask,

301
00:18:18,260 --> 00:18:20,140
why did you break up?

302
00:18:21,540 --> 00:18:22,780
Because Lin Zhanqiao believes

303
00:18:22,866 --> 00:18:24,420
that in a relationship, in marriage,

304
00:18:24,420 --> 00:18:25,911
everything should be shared.

305
00:18:26,420 --> 00:18:26,860
Money,

306
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:28,700
house, car,

307
00:18:29,820 --> 00:18:31,260
time, thoughts, and everything.

308
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:32,940
But He Han believes

309
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,330
that in a relationship, in marriage,

310
00:18:34,340 --> 00:18:35,622
it simply means I love you.

311
00:18:36,340 --> 00:18:37,300
But you

312
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:39,620
seem like an independent woman, Ms. Lin.

313
00:18:41,940 --> 00:18:43,900
That has nothing
to do with independence.

314
00:18:47,540 --> 00:18:48,060
Independence

315
00:18:50,180 --> 00:18:51,700
is something everyone has

316
00:18:52,580 --> 00:18:53,580
once they enter society.

317
00:18:57,540 --> 00:18:58,540
After eighteen,

318
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:00,340
men and women,

319
00:19:00,955 --> 00:19:02,177
before or after marriage,

320
00:19:02,355 --> 00:19:03,444
it's the same, right?

321
00:19:06,340 --> 00:19:06,820
But then,

322
00:19:07,288 --> 00:19:08,700
why do we call love and marriage

323
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:10,300
an intimate relationship?

324
00:19:15,220 --> 00:19:16,380
If two independent people

325
00:19:18,420 --> 00:19:20,300
want to enter into intimacy,

326
00:19:21,060 --> 00:19:22,660
they first have to be close.

327
00:19:23,980 --> 00:19:25,300
Because this kind of relationship

328
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:27,380
is unlike any other.

329
00:19:28,244 --> 00:19:30,133
Even different from the relationship

330
00:19:30,420 --> 00:19:31,955
you have with your parents as an adult.

331
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:36,060
So what Mr. He Han means is

332
00:19:38,222 --> 00:19:39,511
just saying "I love you,"

333
00:19:40,180 --> 00:19:41,860
and everything else is optional?

334
00:19:44,740 --> 00:19:45,940
My question is,

335
00:19:47,460 --> 00:19:48,820
what defines intimacy?

336
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,100
Some people enter a relationship

337
00:19:53,355 --> 00:19:54,644
but are not truly close at all.

338
00:20:04,355 --> 00:20:05,311
I just opened it.

339
00:20:05,420 --> 00:20:06,355
Hurry and try it.

340
00:20:07,977 --> 00:20:09,977
I was worried you
might be in a bad mood,

341
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,311
so I brought a good bottle for you.

342
00:20:19,380 --> 00:20:21,180
Can you tell me honestly?

343
00:20:21,660 --> 00:20:23,400
You're helping Lin Zhanqiao this much,

344
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:25,200
so what are you after?

345
00:20:29,180 --> 00:20:30,940
I want her to owe me a favor.

346
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:32,700
So if I need something later,

347
00:20:33,140 --> 00:20:34,220
she can pay me back.

348
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:36,933
I didn't lie.

349
00:20:38,777 --> 00:20:39,622
You haven't

350
00:20:40,288 --> 00:20:42,355
figured out
how she'll repay you yet

351
00:20:43,022 --> 00:20:44,511
and you're helping her first?

352
00:20:44,620 --> 00:20:47,340
This doesn't quite add up, right?

353
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:06,244
(Campus Spotlight, Gathering of Talents,
No. 54 Middle School,)

354
00:21:06,244 --> 00:21:08,100
(Class of 2013,
Outstanding Alumni, Wang Hai)

355
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,820
(Wang Hai, writing as Gu Yan)

356
00:21:14,780 --> 00:21:15,380
What's wrong?

357
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:22,460
Your writing career
is getting more successful.

358
00:21:24,260 --> 00:21:25,140
I'm happy for you.

359
00:21:27,700 --> 00:21:28,980
I hope you keep getting better.

360
00:21:30,022 --> 00:21:32,111
But at the same time,
I'm afraid you'll get better.

361
00:21:35,540 --> 00:21:36,500
Because before,

362
00:21:36,780 --> 00:21:37,940
we were struggling together.

363
00:21:39,780 --> 00:21:41,220
Now we can't succeed together.

364
00:21:42,822 --> 00:21:44,000
If you succeed,

365
00:21:44,820 --> 00:21:45,460
we won't.

366
00:21:45,980 --> 00:21:47,060
No.

367
00:21:47,380 --> 00:21:48,340
We'll all be fine.

368
00:21:52,260 --> 00:21:53,300
Then tell me,

369
00:21:53,933 --> 00:21:56,111
how are we supposed to be fine together?

370
00:21:57,100 --> 00:21:58,140
If I make it,

371
00:21:58,780 --> 00:22:00,460
I'll have money and opportunities

372
00:22:00,622 --> 00:22:02,355
to bring you all along with me.

373
00:22:03,580 --> 00:22:04,580
Back then,

374
00:22:05,020 --> 00:22:06,820
we shared the hard times.

375
00:22:07,660 --> 00:22:08,140
Now,

376
00:22:08,444 --> 00:22:09,977
we'll share the good times.

377
00:22:11,244 --> 00:22:13,111
I'm not cut out for
enjoying that kind of life.

378
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:17,100
I just want to stay here like this.

379
00:22:23,020 --> 00:22:23,780
What if

380
00:22:24,622 --> 00:22:26,340
the one sharing the good times with you

381
00:22:27,888 --> 00:22:29,333
ends up being someone else?

382
00:22:29,860 --> 00:22:31,180
What are you talking about?

383
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:35,020
Like Lin Zhanqiao.

384
00:22:40,780 --> 00:22:42,340
I know you don't like her.

385
00:22:43,580 --> 00:22:44,900
She looks down on Er Jiu and me.

386
00:22:46,088 --> 00:22:47,933
She looks down on this internet cafe.

387
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:50,020
She thinks we'll hold you back.

388
00:22:51,511 --> 00:22:53,500
Sooner or later,
she'll take you away from us.

389
00:22:53,860 --> 00:22:55,420
She never said that.

390
00:22:55,620 --> 00:22:57,100
And I've never thought that either.

391
00:23:01,140 --> 00:23:02,300
Then, prove it to me.

392
00:23:05,180 --> 00:23:07,260
Isn't my being here right now proof?

393
00:23:07,688 --> 00:23:09,355
What more do you want me to do?

394
00:23:09,780 --> 00:23:11,740
What, you want me to stop writing

395
00:23:11,844 --> 00:23:13,444
and come back to be a manager here?

396
00:23:15,860 --> 00:23:16,460
If that

397
00:23:18,660 --> 00:23:19,300
were the case,

398
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:22,020
would you do it?

399
00:23:28,140 --> 00:23:29,020
No.

400
00:23:31,340 --> 00:23:33,500
Whether it's writing online fiction
or managing a cafe,

401
00:23:35,100 --> 00:23:37,200
isn't it all for making money
and living better?

402
00:23:37,688 --> 00:23:39,866
What's wrong with
choosing whatever earns more?

403
00:23:46,660 --> 00:23:48,100
All you think about is yourself.

404
00:23:50,380 --> 00:23:51,940
You don't want to leave this place,

405
00:23:52,900 --> 00:23:53,980
so you expect everyone else

406
00:23:54,180 --> 00:23:55,500
to stay here with you

407
00:23:55,755 --> 00:23:57,222
and work at this cafe forever.

408
00:23:58,177 --> 00:24:00,333
Aren't you also just
thinking about yourself?

409
00:25:11,155 --> 00:25:12,977
Register at the counter
before logging in.

410
00:25:34,740 --> 00:25:35,140
Hello.

411
00:25:35,900 --> 00:25:36,620
4893.

412
00:25:39,740 --> 00:25:40,260
Let's go.

413
00:26:03,460 --> 00:26:03,980
Hey,

414
00:26:04,340 --> 00:26:05,500
do you know what kind of car

415
00:26:05,500 --> 00:26:06,977
I got a ride in after work today?

416
00:26:06,980 --> 00:26:08,100
I'll send you a picture.

417
00:26:10,780 --> 00:26:12,620
Sir, you can just pull over ahead.

418
00:26:12,820 --> 00:26:13,180
Alright.

419
00:26:15,260 --> 00:26:15,940
Sure thing.

420
00:26:17,100 --> 00:26:17,620
Thanks.

421
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:19,330
Please give a good rating.

422
00:26:19,330 --> 00:26:19,900
Of course.

423
00:26:44,980 --> 00:26:46,980
(Legend: Meet at the corner cafe
on Fuxing Road.)

424
00:27:20,060 --> 00:27:20,980
Mr. He Han.

425
00:27:21,500 --> 00:27:22,420
Here. Sit.

426
00:27:24,511 --> 00:27:26,220
I'm not sure what you young people like,

427
00:27:26,220 --> 00:27:27,180
so I just ordered a bit.

428
00:27:27,300 --> 00:27:28,380
Thank you, Mr. He Han.

429
00:27:28,644 --> 00:27:30,700
I asked you out,
so I should be the one treating.

430
00:27:31,180 --> 00:27:31,900
Forget it.

431
00:27:32,044 --> 00:27:33,755
You can't even afford rent right now.

432
00:27:36,220 --> 00:27:36,980
Go on,

433
00:27:37,460 --> 00:27:38,580
what's so urgent?

434
00:27:40,300 --> 00:27:41,180
It's like this.

435
00:27:42,060 --> 00:27:43,260
At the company,

436
00:27:43,311 --> 00:27:45,466
I've started handling
the selection of new authors.

437
00:27:45,620 --> 00:27:47,380
But when it comes to the criteria,

438
00:27:47,860 --> 00:27:49,000
it always feels like

439
00:27:49,044 --> 00:27:51,100
something is off here or there.

440
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:55,444
Have you met them in person?

441
00:27:56,020 --> 00:27:56,460
No.

442
00:27:57,177 --> 00:27:59,111
Don't you usually read
their submissions first?

443
00:27:59,260 --> 00:28:00,100
Meet them more.

444
00:28:00,777 --> 00:28:02,200
If their abilities are about the same,

445
00:28:02,220 --> 00:28:03,500
pick the better-looking one

446
00:28:03,500 --> 00:28:04,688
with a nicer temperament.

447
00:28:05,060 --> 00:28:06,740
What does being good-looking matter?

448
00:28:07,100 --> 00:28:08,260
You'll have to work with them.

449
00:28:08,340 --> 00:28:10,060
You'll be in contact
every day for years.

450
00:28:11,140 --> 00:28:12,250
If they look better,

451
00:28:12,250 --> 00:28:13,660
won't it put you in a better mood?

452
00:28:14,980 --> 00:28:16,180
That actually makes some sense.

453
00:28:19,620 --> 00:28:20,288
Anything else?

454
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:20,980
That's it?

455
00:28:21,533 --> 00:28:23,066
You were in such a hurry to see me

456
00:28:23,088 --> 00:28:24,711
just to ask something like this?

457
00:28:27,733 --> 00:28:28,980
Is your boss treating you badly?

458
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:30,220
No.

459
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:32,050
Are you not used to living at her place?

460
00:28:32,060 --> 00:28:32,420
No.

461
00:28:32,740 --> 00:28:33,860
Then, what could it be?

462
00:28:39,140 --> 00:28:39,580
Fine.

463
00:28:39,700 --> 00:28:41,111
If you won't say it, I'm leaving.

464
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:42,340
Mr. He Han,

465
00:28:45,580 --> 00:28:45,900
I'm here

466
00:28:46,580 --> 00:28:48,060
on behalf of your readers

467
00:28:48,540 --> 00:28:49,860
to check on you.

468
00:28:51,060 --> 00:28:53,700
We're worried you might stop updating
or stop writing altogether.

469
00:28:58,980 --> 00:29:00,488
You mean what happened this morning?

470
00:29:04,940 --> 00:29:05,660
Mr. He Han,

471
00:29:06,340 --> 00:29:08,260
this really isn't a big deal.

472
00:29:08,980 --> 00:29:09,980
In our hearts,

473
00:29:09,980 --> 00:29:11,180
you'll always be number one.

474
00:29:11,540 --> 00:29:13,500
Even if one day,
something happens again,

475
00:29:13,580 --> 00:29:14,340
or one day,

476
00:29:15,420 --> 00:29:16,300
you stop writing,

477
00:29:16,300 --> 00:29:18,222
and your name
is no longer on the charts,

478
00:29:19,220 --> 00:29:20,020
to us,

479
00:29:20,020 --> 00:29:21,540
you'll still be like a legend.

480
00:29:23,700 --> 00:29:24,220
Thank you.

481
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:26,700
Although I think

482
00:29:26,700 --> 00:29:28,266
you could've just sent that on WeChat,

483
00:29:28,340 --> 00:29:29,340
thank you anyway.

484
00:29:29,488 --> 00:29:30,800
Thank you, all of you.

485
00:29:35,980 --> 00:29:36,300
I...

486
00:29:37,660 --> 00:29:40,260
I was just worried you'd
be in a bad mood today,

487
00:29:42,580 --> 00:29:43,220
feeling down.

488
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:55,140
Do you really think that little of me?

489
00:29:57,500 --> 00:29:59,700
Any author who has made it this far

490
00:29:59,700 --> 00:30:01,180
is tough enough to take a beating.

491
00:30:02,060 --> 00:30:03,660
Do I seem that fragile to you?

492
00:30:06,340 --> 00:30:06,740
So,

493
00:30:07,220 --> 00:30:09,340
can we still expect regular updates?

494
00:30:09,660 --> 00:30:11,620
Are you worried about the novel or me?

495
00:30:14,580 --> 00:30:15,420
Both.

496
00:30:16,540 --> 00:30:17,300
Don't worry.

497
00:30:18,140 --> 00:30:20,740
I'll keep updating
like the sun rises every day.

498
00:30:22,900 --> 00:30:23,260
Alright.

499
00:30:23,900 --> 00:30:24,460
Eat.

500
00:30:24,540 --> 00:30:25,733
I'll take you back after.

501
00:30:26,300 --> 00:30:26,660
Okay.

502
00:30:35,020 --> 00:30:35,860
This is really good.

503
00:30:54,180 --> 00:30:54,888
Where's Zhangzhu?

504
00:30:55,060 --> 00:30:55,700
Still asleep?

505
00:31:04,644 --> 00:31:06,200
Have you decided what to wear?

506
00:31:07,100 --> 00:31:07,777
What is it?

507
00:31:08,866 --> 00:31:10,800
Don't you have
a date in a couple of days?

508
00:31:10,860 --> 00:31:11,860
Pick out something nice.

509
00:31:12,660 --> 00:31:13,660
I don't even want to go.

510
00:31:14,822 --> 00:31:16,420
Even though the match rate is already

511
00:31:16,420 --> 00:31:17,380
ninety percent,

512
00:31:17,980 --> 00:31:20,100
that remaining ten percent

513
00:31:20,460 --> 00:31:22,140
has a major issue.

514
00:31:22,740 --> 00:31:23,380
What issue?

515
00:31:24,155 --> 00:31:25,511
Sleeping in separate rooms?

516
00:31:27,900 --> 00:31:28,740
He has a child,

517
00:31:29,244 --> 00:31:30,777
but the child doesn't live with him.

518
00:31:32,260 --> 00:31:33,333
What does he look like?

519
00:31:34,580 --> 00:31:35,980
From the avatar, he looks okay.

520
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:37,140
No photos?

521
00:31:37,955 --> 00:31:39,860
The platform doesn't
want us judging by looks,

522
00:31:39,860 --> 00:31:40,460
so basically,

523
00:31:40,700 --> 00:31:42,300
it matches you based on

524
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:43,220
the height and weight

525
00:31:43,820 --> 00:31:44,740
you provide.

526
00:31:45,660 --> 00:31:47,100
Even the avatar is generated by AI

527
00:31:47,740 --> 00:31:49,620
based on your real-life photos.

528
00:31:50,060 --> 00:31:50,580
So the idea

529
00:31:50,780 --> 00:31:53,140
is matching lifestyle and mindset.

530
00:31:54,180 --> 00:31:55,180
Then, just go meet him.

531
00:31:55,533 --> 00:31:56,800
He might be decent, right?

532
00:31:57,140 --> 00:31:58,620
If he's not, message me,

533
00:31:58,666 --> 00:32:00,044
and I'll come rescue you.

534
00:32:00,533 --> 00:32:02,111
You haven't had plans at night lately?

535
00:32:02,260 --> 00:32:02,620
No.

536
00:32:03,266 --> 00:32:04,755
You haven't contacted Lawyer Bei?

537
00:32:04,980 --> 00:32:06,311
He hasn't contacted you either?

538
00:32:08,060 --> 00:32:08,380
No.

539
00:32:10,260 --> 00:32:11,100
Don't see him.

540
00:32:12,540 --> 00:32:13,980
If being together makes you unhappy,

541
00:32:14,620 --> 00:32:15,860
then now is the best time

542
00:32:16,333 --> 00:32:18,577
to cut things off completely.
Don't meet him again.

543
00:32:20,100 --> 00:32:20,700
I promise.

544
00:32:23,580 --> 00:32:24,660
Pick out a nice outfit.

545
00:32:24,822 --> 00:32:26,711
What if he turns out to be good-looking?

546
00:32:32,333 --> 00:32:33,533
Is it Lawyer Bei?

547
00:32:39,460 --> 00:32:39,980
He said

548
00:32:40,266 --> 00:32:42,288
let's have lunch on Saturday at noon.

549
00:32:43,060 --> 00:32:44,460
You just promised me

550
00:32:45,333 --> 00:32:46,333
you wouldn't go.

551
00:32:48,940 --> 00:32:49,340
I won't.

552
00:32:51,020 --> 00:32:52,860
He can't just act
as if nothing happened.

553
00:32:53,500 --> 00:32:55,380
Right now, he's trying to control you,

554
00:32:55,800 --> 00:32:57,311
trying to manipulate you.

555
00:32:57,380 --> 00:32:58,300
If you go,

556
00:32:58,660 --> 00:33:00,155
you'll fall right into his trap.

557
00:33:15,500 --> 00:33:17,100
(Have lunch together Saturday at noon?)

558
00:33:17,100 --> 00:33:18,900
(I have plans on Saturday.
Sorry, I won't be able to make it.)

559
00:33:30,100 --> 00:33:34,060
(Zhou Mei: Okay, see you Saturday.)

560
00:34:31,540 --> 00:34:32,020
Hello?

561
00:34:32,900 --> 00:34:33,380
Mr. He,

562
00:34:33,430 --> 00:34:35,577
the two boxes of beer
have been delivered to your door.

563
00:34:36,700 --> 00:34:38,060
What beer? I didn't order anything.

564
00:35:11,620 --> 00:35:12,466
This is pretty good.

565
00:35:12,860 --> 00:35:13,911
Meals and lodging included.

566
00:35:13,940 --> 00:35:14,620
For how long?

567
00:35:15,380 --> 00:35:15,980
For life.

568
00:35:18,020 --> 00:35:18,660
Single room?

569
00:35:18,980 --> 00:35:19,460
Double.

570
00:35:21,660 --> 00:35:22,780
Three hundred a day?

571
00:35:23,940 --> 00:35:25,700
There's a mahjong room
and nursing staff.

572
00:35:25,900 --> 00:35:26,820
Then 350.

573
00:35:27,620 --> 00:35:28,777
That's 10,000 a month,

574
00:35:28,820 --> 00:35:29,780
120,000 a year.

575
00:35:29,955 --> 00:35:31,460
Even if you live another ten years,

576
00:35:31,620 --> 00:35:33,133
that's only about 1.2 million.

577
00:35:35,311 --> 00:35:36,644
I don't live that long.

578
00:35:36,820 --> 00:35:38,444
Then, it won't even reach that.

579
00:35:39,060 --> 00:35:40,540
How much is your place worth anyway?

580
00:35:40,860 --> 00:35:41,844
It's old and run down,

581
00:35:41,850 --> 00:35:43,650
but it should still sell
for two or three million.

582
00:35:43,660 --> 00:35:45,511
The housing market
isn't great right now.

583
00:35:45,822 --> 00:35:47,720
The retirement home
is offering 300,000 in cash.

584
00:35:47,740 --> 00:35:48,540
300,000?

585
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:50,888
You're getting ripped off,
you know that?

586
00:35:51,060 --> 00:35:51,860
It's my place.

587
00:35:52,020 --> 00:35:53,644
I can do whatever I want with it.

588
00:35:55,060 --> 00:35:55,860
Fine, suit yourself.

589
00:35:56,644 --> 00:35:57,850
Living that far away works too.

590
00:35:57,860 --> 00:35:59,400
No one's going to visit you anyway.

591
00:36:01,900 --> 00:36:03,022
At the retirement home,

592
00:36:03,220 --> 00:36:04,380
I filled out my profile.

593
00:36:04,980 --> 00:36:05,420
No family.

594
00:36:05,940 --> 00:36:06,580
No children.

595
00:36:07,140 --> 00:36:07,740
That's great.

596
00:36:09,511 --> 00:36:11,244
So why are you looking for me?

597
00:36:23,700 --> 00:36:24,980
I sorted these out while moving.

598
00:36:25,066 --> 00:36:26,600
See if there's anything you still want.

599
00:36:26,610 --> 00:36:27,711
If not, I'll throw them away.

600
00:36:31,977 --> 00:36:33,533
I didn't even want to bring them.

601
00:36:33,600 --> 00:36:35,733
What's the point of
keeping them after someone dies?

602
00:36:35,822 --> 00:36:37,133
Out of sight, out of mind.

603
00:36:41,088 --> 00:36:42,380
You'll be dead soon enough, too.

604
00:36:42,640 --> 00:36:44,288
When you die, I'll burn all your things

605
00:36:44,333 --> 00:36:45,260
for you right away.

606
00:36:45,777 --> 00:36:47,140
If you leave even a scrap behind,

607
00:36:47,220 --> 00:36:48,422
you're no better than an animal.

608
00:36:49,220 --> 00:36:50,900
Don't even put my photo on my grave.

609
00:36:51,422 --> 00:36:52,940
When I die, just let me have some peace.

610
00:36:53,100 --> 00:36:54,860
Don't worry.
No one will visit you anyway.

611
00:36:54,980 --> 00:36:56,940
You don't even need a grave,
let alone a photo.

612
00:36:56,940 --> 00:36:58,755
When I die,
I won't have anyone notify you.

613
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:00,500
You might as well
consider me dead already.

614
00:37:00,500 --> 00:37:02,500
If you hadn't come today,
I already would have.

615
00:37:56,300 --> 00:37:56,620
Come.

616
00:37:58,300 --> 00:37:59,660
It's always lively here.

617
00:38:02,620 --> 00:38:03,620
Miss, come.

618
00:38:04,060 --> 00:38:04,420
Let's go.

619
00:38:04,820 --> 00:38:06,580
This is the place I mentioned.

620
00:38:11,220 --> 00:38:12,060
It's this one.

621
00:38:15,380 --> 00:38:15,980
Miss,

622
00:38:17,020 --> 00:38:18,140
are you really not afraid?

623
00:38:19,300 --> 00:38:20,980
If the price is low enough, I'm not.

624
00:38:21,460 --> 00:38:21,980
Alright.

625
00:38:22,100 --> 00:38:23,200
I'll take you upstairs.

626
00:38:26,020 --> 00:38:27,660
This house is over 100 years old.

627
00:38:27,740 --> 00:38:29,900
Thirty square meters of living space.

628
00:38:30,220 --> 00:38:31,300
That's already pretty good.

629
00:38:31,540 --> 00:38:33,700
Men and women
who've come to see it before

630
00:38:33,980 --> 00:38:35,740
all backed out because they were scared.

631
00:38:36,340 --> 00:38:37,700
But if you think about it,

632
00:38:38,380 --> 00:38:39,620
old houses like this

633
00:38:39,620 --> 00:38:41,180
are bound to have things.

634
00:38:41,700 --> 00:38:43,060
I'm a straightforward person.

635
00:38:43,380 --> 00:38:44,540
When people come to view it,

636
00:38:44,740 --> 00:38:46,220
I tell them honestly.

637
00:38:46,540 --> 00:38:47,140
Otherwise,

638
00:38:47,500 --> 00:38:48,980
they will blame me later.

639
00:38:49,140 --> 00:38:49,740
Right?

640
00:38:50,140 --> 00:38:50,460
Come.

641
00:38:53,220 --> 00:38:53,900
This is the room.

642
00:39:31,380 --> 00:39:32,540
Why are you still here?

643
00:39:35,066 --> 00:39:37,644
I can't move into the retirement
home until the day after tomorrow.

644
00:39:38,060 --> 00:39:39,580
Why not stay home a couple more days?

645
00:39:40,340 --> 00:39:41,540
I miscalculated the dates.

646
00:39:42,044 --> 00:39:44,380
After signing the contract,
it was supposed to be 30 days,

647
00:39:44,666 --> 00:39:46,200
or a few days, before moving in.

648
00:39:46,860 --> 00:39:48,220
So I contacted the retirement home.

649
00:39:48,420 --> 00:39:49,420
Move in after 30 days.

650
00:39:49,620 --> 00:39:51,060
Who knew I got the days wrong?

651
00:39:52,511 --> 00:39:54,066
Where are you planning to stay?

652
00:39:54,420 --> 00:39:54,980
Here.

653
00:39:55,066 --> 00:39:56,444
Otherwise, why would I come to you?

654
00:39:56,460 --> 00:39:58,400
Didn't you say you
came to give me the photos?

655
00:39:58,700 --> 00:40:00,860
Those old photos
aren't worth a special trip.

656
00:40:04,020 --> 00:40:04,340
Fine.

657
00:40:14,660 --> 00:40:15,060
Get up.

658
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:18,822
What are you doing?

659
00:40:19,060 --> 00:40:19,580
Come on.

660
00:40:19,580 --> 00:40:21,180
Take your things and come with me.

661
00:40:23,800 --> 00:40:24,866
You're kicking me out?

662
00:40:25,260 --> 00:40:25,820
Listen,

663
00:40:25,940 --> 00:40:26,580
I'm your father.

664
00:40:26,711 --> 00:40:28,244
If you kick me out, I'll call the police

665
00:40:28,250 --> 00:40:29,880
to report
that you're abusing the elderly.

666
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:30,860
Come downstairs with me.

667
00:40:30,860 --> 00:40:32,866
I'll get you a room
at the front desk, okay?

668
00:40:39,140 --> 00:40:41,140
(Name: He Wei)

669
00:40:44,380 --> 00:40:45,660
You really got 300,000 in cash?

670
00:40:46,177 --> 00:40:47,200
Why would I lie to you?

671
00:40:47,700 --> 00:40:48,700
Did you bring the money?

672
00:40:49,220 --> 00:40:50,511
Don't get scammed again.

673
00:40:53,820 --> 00:40:55,100
It's all in the card, every cent.

674
00:40:55,300 --> 00:40:56,044
Let me see.

675
00:40:58,577 --> 00:40:59,577
What are you doing?

676
00:40:59,644 --> 00:41:00,511
Paying for the room.

677
00:41:00,644 --> 00:41:01,780
Why should I pay?

678
00:41:01,780 --> 00:41:03,355
If you stay in a hotel without paying,

679
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:04,444
they'll call the police.

680
00:41:04,580 --> 00:41:05,100
You...

681
00:41:05,260 --> 00:41:07,060
Didn't you say you had
300,000 in your card?

682
00:41:08,820 --> 00:41:10,340
Mr. He, the deposit is two thousand.

683
00:41:38,060 --> 00:41:38,940
(Incorrect password limit exceeded)

684
00:41:51,860 --> 00:41:52,820
Think carefully.

685
00:41:52,888 --> 00:41:55,155
One more wrong attempt,
and your card will be locked.

686
00:42:11,300 --> 00:42:12,140
Later, have the staff

687
00:42:12,220 --> 00:42:14,000
bring up the two cases
of beer I ordered.

688
00:42:17,020 --> 00:42:17,660
Hey,

689
00:42:17,940 --> 00:42:18,977
where's Lin Zhanqiao?

690
00:42:24,180 --> 00:42:24,700
We broke up.

691
00:42:26,580 --> 00:42:27,466
I'm warning you,

692
00:42:27,844 --> 00:42:29,155
don't go looking for her.

693
00:42:29,940 --> 00:42:32,060
How could you have broken up?

694
00:42:32,577 --> 00:42:34,220
If she doesn't
follow you around all day,

695
00:42:34,220 --> 00:42:36,288
talking non-stop, she can't
even get through a day.

696
00:42:36,660 --> 00:42:37,260
Don't worry.

697
00:42:37,644 --> 00:42:39,733
Whether you broke up or not,
I'll go find her.

698
00:42:39,800 --> 00:42:40,533
Because only she

699
00:42:40,620 --> 00:42:42,100
is willing to treat me to good drinks.

700
00:42:42,580 --> 00:42:44,900
So don't try to scare me
with that breakup talk.

701
00:42:45,511 --> 00:42:46,422
We really broke up.

702
00:42:48,540 --> 00:42:49,300
I'll say it again.

703
00:42:49,644 --> 00:42:50,911
Don't go looking for her.

704
00:42:51,020 --> 00:42:52,311
Don't make a fool of yourself.

705
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

706
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

707
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

708
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

709
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

710
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

711
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

712
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

713
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

714
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

715
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

716
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

717
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

718
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

719
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

720
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

721
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

722
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

723
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

724
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

725
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

726
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

727
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

728
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

729
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

730
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

731
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

732
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

733
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

734
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

735
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

736
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

737
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

738
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

739
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

740
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

741
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
